This Privacy Policy provides information about how wavve Americas, Inc. (“we”, “us”, or “our”) collects, uses and shares information from you or about you, including your personal information, and your choices. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully before using or accessing the KOCOWA online streaming service, available at the http://www.kocowa.com website (the “Website”) and the KOCOWA mobile application operated by us (collectively, the “Service”).
When you use the Service or access the Website, you consent to the collection, use and sharing of information from you or about you in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
1. Information We Collect
a. We collect all information you provide to us, which includes, without limitation, your name, email address, home address, date of birth, gender, telephone number, and your preferences. If you buy the Service, we will also collect your credit card information, which includes the billing address associated with your credit card.
b. In addition, we collect usage information through various technologies. For instance, usage information includes information about your internet browser, computer operating system, the web and app pages you viewed, your IP address or other unique identifiers of the computer, mobile device or other devices that you use in connection with the Service or the Website.
c. We do not knowingly collect information about individuals under the age of 18, or under the age of majority in the domicile of such individuals. We will delete such information after we are notified that such user is under the age of 18, or if we become actually aware of such fact by other means.
2. How We Collect Information
a. We collect information from or about you in various ways. For instance, and without limitation, we collect information from you, when you sign up for the Service on the Website.
b. We also collect information from or about you from any interactions with us, the Website or the Service, such as, without limitation, when you:
– submit an inquiry to us;
– take part in any online survey made available by us;
– communicate with us for any matter by, without limitation, email, regular mail, facsimile or telephone;
– use the Service via SNS (e.g., Facebook);
– access the Website or the Service through a third party website; and
– use Service features such as search functions.
c. We use technologies such as cookies to collect your usage information. A cookie is a small data file that is transferred to your computer’s hard disk. Cookies may be used for many purposes. For instance, cookies may be used to remember you and your preferences on the Website, track your activities in connection with your use of the Service and the Website, and maintain a history of using the Service for you.
d. In addition to the cookies, we use technology such as web beacons, third party advertising servers, Google Analytics, Mobile Device, Embedded Scripts, and others to collect the usage information
including your name, contact information, browsing history, viewing history, and purchase history.
e. When you log onto the Service or Website using a third-party Single Sign On (“SSO”) service (e.g., Google, Apple, Meta, or On Demand Korea), we will collect your personal information from those third parties. This personal information may include your name, birth date, location, marital status, occupation, and any other personal information you have disclosed to these third parties.
3. How We Use Information
a. We use information from or about you, as reasonably necessary in our sole discretion to deliver and improve the Service and the Website.
b. In addition, we may use information from or about you in, without limitation, the following:
To fulfill or meet the reason for which the information is provided. For example, if you provide us with personal information in order for us to create your user account, we will use that information to verify your user account as necessary after such account is created and communicate with you.
To send promotional materials to you
To select and announce the event winners
To customize the advertisements delivered to you
To process payments for the Service
To conduct surveys or to do researches
To prevent unauthorized use of the Service or the Website and other ways described in the Privacy Policy or as we may notify you from time to time
To provide you with support and to respond to your inquiries, including to investigate and address your concerns and monitor and improve our responses.
To respond to law enforcement requests and as required by applicable law, court order, or governmental regulations.
As described to you when collecting your personal information or as otherwise set forth in the CCPA.
To evaluate or conduct a merger, divestiture, restructuring, reorganization, dissolution, or other sale or transfer of some or all of our assets, whether as a going concern or as part of bankruptcy, liquidation, or similar proceeding, in which personal information held by us is among the assets transferred.
c. All information we collect from or about you may be combined with additional information from our vendors and affiliates to improve the Service and the Website.
d. When you log onto the Service or Website using a third-party SSO service, we may use the personal information we collected from the third party to create a more personalized and targeted viewing and advertising experience for you.
e. We use information collected via Meta Pixel about your use of the Website, including your browsing history, viewing history, and purchase history, to create a personalized and targeted viewing and advertising experience for you.
4. How We Share Information
a. We may share information from or about you with third parties, including our business partners or affiliates in order to provide the Service to you and their services to us. Such third parties, business partners or affiliates may include, without limitation, social networking service providers, advertisers, advertising and related service providers, IT service providers, and marketing service providers. However, you may opt out from receiving targeted advertisements from advertisers by clicking the opt-out links below.
* NAI:
http://optout. networkadvertising.org/?c=1
* DAA:
http://optout.aboutads.info/? c=2&lang=EN
b. We may share your information with our affiliates for business and for operational purposes.
c. We may disclose information from or about you when required by law to do so.
d. Information that we collect from or about you may be transferred to, and stored in the United States of America by us. The third parties, business partners or affiliates described above may be located in the United States of America or abroad, and they may store your information in the United States or abroad. This means your information may be processed globally. By using the Service and the Website, you consent to the international transfer, storing and processing of your information, if any.
e. When you log onto the Service or Website using a third-party SSO service, we may share your viewing history with the third-party SSO service you have chosen to use.
f. We share your browsing, viewing, and purchase history collected using Meta Pixel with Meta so that we can provide you with a more targeted and personalized viewing and advertising experience.
5. Security
a. We employ reasonable technical, contractual, administrative, and physical security steps to protect information from or about you. Data transferred and accessible over the internet, however, cannot be 100% secure regardless of the security measures employed. Accordingly, we cannot guarantee the security of your information.
b. You may access some of the information that we collect from or about you by accessing the [
my account page
] on our Website. You may verify the accuracy of your information and update as necessary through your account settings at the [
my account page
] on our Website.
6. Changes to Privacy Policy
a. We may, from time to time, change this Privacy Policy. Such changes shall be effective at the time indicated in the notice that we send to you, whether by email or otherwise.
b. Your continued use of the Service after notice of the Privacy Policy changes and after the changes are scheduled to take effect, constitutes your acceptance of the changes thereto.  If you refuse to accept such changes to the Privacy Policy, you may cancel your use of the Service.
7. Governing Law
a. This Privacy Policy shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of California without reference to rules on the conflicts of laws.
b. Any and all disputes arising hereunder or related hereto shall be resolved exclusively in the State and Federal Courts located in Los Angeles, California, and the parties hereto consent to the exclusive personal and subject matter jurisdiction of such courts.
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, or wish to withdraw your consent to our use of your information, please contact us via e-mail at: privacy@kocowa.com. You may also contact us via regular mail at: wavve Americas, Inc, 625 S Kingsley DR #2F Los Angeles CA 90005-2319.
